  static const String tutorialSemanticsEng = '''
The Uni-Voice Blind App is an app that reads the voice code Uni-Voice, developed for people with visual impairment. 
Please hold your smartphone at a height of 10cm and let the Uni-Voice voice code appears on the screen. 
The app will automatically take a picture and read out the content. 
The location of the Uni-Voice voice code is indicated by the cutout on the printed material. Turn the device around so that the cut is on the lower right side. The Uni-Voice voice code will be printed right next to the cutout. 

The Uni-Voice Blind App also provides notifications for the visually impaired from government offices and municipalities. Please refer to the list of announcements screen. 
The new Uni-Voice codes include a navigation code that provides route location information to the destination using voice, sound and vibration, and a spot code that guides and provides information on evacuation sites and tourist facilities. For more details, please refer to the usage instruction screen in the app text. 

Uni-Voice Blind App Manual

1. How to read the voice code Uni-Voice
When you start the app, the reading screen will appear. 
Put your smartphone at a height of about 10cm (about the width of a man's fist) and place the Uni-Voice code on the screen. 
The key to reading the code is to match the height of the voice code with the height of the smartphone's camera. 
When the voice code appears on the screen, a shutter sound will automatically be heard and the voice code will be scanned. 
If it is too dark or too bright, a buzzer sound will be emitted, so please adjust the brightness. 
The text information of the scanned voice code will be automatically saved. 

2. Reading out the voice code Uni-Voice
When the voice code Uni-Voice is successfully read, the reading screen will automatically appear. 
If you have turned on the accessibility function (voice over) of your device, the read text information will be displayed in the center of the reading screen. 
If the accessibility function (voice over) is set to off, the voice reading will be performed automatically

3. 
The file recall screen will be displayed in date order. 
Slide through the lines to delete, modify, or select and copy all of the text. 
(For voice over setting, flick down)

4. Save scanned files
Scanned voice codes will be saved automatically. 
The saved file name will be the first 16 characters of the character information. 

5. Delete the scanned file or change the file name
Tap the Delete button on the readout screen. 
To rename a file, tap the file name text field in the readout screen to change it. 
You can also do this by sliding the line in the call list screen. 

6. Send scanned text via email
Tap the Send Email button on the reading screen. 
The email application will launch and the text information will be pasted into the body of the message. 

7. Transfer scanned text information to other apps
Tap the Select All Copy button on the text-to-speech screen. 
All text information will be copied and pasted into other applications. 

8. For continuous scanning
Tap the Settings button on the menu screen to turn on the continuous scanning setting. 

9. Camera illumination
If your device has a camera illumination (light), please turn on the setting depending on the brightness. 

10. Sign language setting
If sign language information is recorded in the voice code, turn on the sign language setting to play the sign language video. 

11. No Sound Setting
If you are bothered by the beeping sound on the scanning screen, please turn it on. If you are concerned about the beeping sound on the scan screen, please turn it on. The beeping sound will stop when the app starts. 

12. Language Settings
If other language information is recorded in the voice code, please change the language settings. 

13. How not to receive notifications
Notifications in this app use iOS notifications. 
Turn off notifications by tapping Univoice Blind in iOS settings. If you turn it off, you won't receive any notifications. 
If you are using voice over and your notifications are talking, please go to iOS Settings, Accessibility, and turn off Always Read Notifications for voice over. 

14. How to recall or read out univoice codes previously read by voice input
1)Launch the univoice blind app. 
2)On the beep screen, tap the Go to voice input screen button. 
3)Tap this button in the middle of the screen and tap the "Speak to me" button. 
4)Talk to your iPhone or iPad and say "Find notes on anything" to see the list. 
5) Talk to your iPhone or iPad and ask it to read out the notes. For example, you can specify the date and time, such as today, yesterday, or the day before yesterday, or you can specify keywords. 

15. Terms of Use
You will be redirected to the Uni-Voice homepage. 
Please read them carefully. 

16. Privacy Policy
Go to the Uni-Voice website. 
Please read it carefully. 

17. Contact Information
